00:28:12.120 --> 00:28:15.590
But I think there are
some key learnings, right,

00:28:15.590 --> 00:28:18.460
in both these two stories.

00:28:18.460 --> 00:28:23.250
So I think person to
person interaction

00:28:23.250 --> 00:28:26.010
does shift social
norms and builds trust.

00:28:26.010 --> 00:28:32.040
And for a lot of
technology adoption,

00:28:32.040 --> 00:28:36.040
it's not just about
technology itself.

00:28:36.040 --> 00:28:37.680
It's about changing mindsets.

00:28:37.680 --> 00:28:40.620
So it's very important
to have that person

00:28:40.620 --> 00:28:42.690
to person interaction.

00:28:42.690 --> 00:28:45.390
And then secondly, which is
very relevant to the first one,

00:28:45.390 --> 00:28:48.690
that it's not just not
the product itself,

00:28:48.690 --> 00:28:51.900
and it's not how we
deliver technology,

00:28:51.900 --> 00:28:54.870
it's actually as
important, if not more

00:28:54.870 --> 00:28:58.120
than the technology itself.

00:28:58.120 --> 00:29:05.640
And the last one is that when
high tech meets high touch,

00:29:05.640 --> 00:29:09.640
the early days of
tech adoption actually

00:29:09.640 --> 00:29:11.650
really happens at that time.

00:29:11.650 --> 00:29:16.560
And I think that's also
where the magic happens.

00:29:16.560 --> 00:29:19.710
And I want to sort
of end on that note

00:29:19.710 --> 00:29:28.050
that, sitting in 2017
right now, there are so

00:29:28.050 --> 00:29:33.000
many immense sort of progress
